{
  "id": 133123,
  "referenceId": 109177,
  "name": "Ruth 3:1–4:22",
  "localizedName": "Ruth 3:1–4:22",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Boaz wasn’t the closest male relative who was responsible for helping Ruth and Naomi. But the man who was their closest family protector hadn’t started helping them yet."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Naomi used her knowledge and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108325",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "wisdom"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " to make a clever plan. Ruth carried out Naomi’s plan. Ruth boldly asked Boaz to act as their family protector. Boaz blessed Ruth for asking him to do this. She was showing him kindness by choosing him instead of another male relative."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Boaz made a wise and clever plan and carried it out right away. The closest family protector didn’t want to be fully responsible for Naomi and Ruth. This allowed Boaz to be their family protector. It allowed him to "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108381",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "buy back"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " or redeem Naomi’s family land. It also allowed him to marry Ruth."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The whole community blessed their "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108206",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "marriage"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and blessed the son born to Ruth and Boaz. Even though Ruth was from Moab, she was considered fully part of "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108302",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "God’s people"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Her son Obed would carry on the name of Ruth’s first husband. Naomi took care of Obed like he was her own son. Obed became the grandfather of King "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108449",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "David"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108220",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "family line"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " shows how David came from the family of Judah, Perez and Ruth. The Gospel of Matthew shows that "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108219",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Jesus"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " came from this same family line (Matthew 1:1–16)."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
